Into which having thus made re-entry, he could not yield again to withdraw, though he saw no encouragement to proceedÍ¾ lest his credit, foiled in his first attempt, in a second should utterly be dis- graced. Between extremities he made a right adventure, putting all to God and good fortuneÍ¾ and, which was worst, refused not to entertain every person and means whatso- ever, to furnish out this expedition, the success whereof hath been declared.

But such is the infinite bounty of God, who from every evil deriveth good.
